Durban - A driver of a bakkie sustained head and chest injuries following a freak accident in Red Hill, Durban, this morning. According to Shawn Herbst from Netcare 911 the back wheel of a minibus taxi had broken off while travelling downhill and crashed through the window of a light delivery vehicle which was parked at a robot. Herbst said the incident took place corners of Blackburn Road and North Coast Road  just after 7:30am. "The driver of the bakkie sustained head and chest injuries from the impact of the wheel and was treated for suspected spinal injuries. "The patient was treated on scene and once stabilised was transported by Netcare 911 ambulance to hospital for further treatment. In a separate accident on Monday Netcare 911 said the driver of a light motor vehicle fled the scene of an accident in Commercial and Pietermaritz Street in Pietermaritzburg. "Reports from the scene indicate that the driver of a light motor vehicle lost control knocking down a traffic light then coming to rest against a wall. "Upon assessment no occupants were found, witnesses said that the driver ran away from the scene." POST 